      <h2>Eligibility for Lifetime Free Cards</h2>
      <p>LTF cards have more accessible eligibility criteria compared to premium cards:</p>

      <ul class="feature-list">
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Age:</strong> 21-60 years for primary cards; some banks offer LTF cards to applicants as young as 18</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Income:</strong> ₹15,000/month minimum for most LTF cards; some require as low as ₹12,000/month</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Credit Score:</strong> 680+ CIBIL for most LTF options; IDFC and AU cards may accept 650+ for existing customers</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Employment:</strong> Salaried employees, self-employed, business owners, students, and freelancers are all eligible</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>First-Time Applicants:</strong> LTF cards are ideal as first credit cards — no prior credit history required for some options</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Documents:</strong> PAN Card, Aadhaar Card, income proof (salary slip or bank statement), and photograph</li>
      </ul>

